This article is a presidential proclamation issued by Barack Obama on August 30, 2013, in honor of Labor Day. The proclamation recognizes the contributions of American workers and their role in shaping the nation's history. It highlights the importance of workers' rights and the need to restore the basic bargain that guarantees fair pay, decent hours, safe working conditions, and a secure retirement. The proclamation also mentions the efforts of the Obama administration to bring back good jobs, expand worker training programs, and eliminate tax breaks for the wealthy. Obama emphasizes his support for collective bargaining rights and a higher minimum wage to strengthen the middle class. He concludes by urging public officials and citizens to observe Labor Day with appropriate programs and activities that honor the resilience of working Americans.